        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 8 at 11:47PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1147 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles south of Lefors, or 14 miles southeast of Pampa, moving south
at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lefors.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 100 AM CDT for
the Panhandle of Texas.</instruction>
